reviews.text: I spent an enjoyable hour here, the 30-40 paintings being exhibited covered the coastline of California.  The exhibition changes at the end of March 2019.
validated parking!! small gallery but definitely worth the visit

I spent a few days in Newport Beach just hanging out I was looking for some interesting things to do and came across the Irvine Museum I'm not an art person but for some reason I really enjoyed this place.  The employees are very friendly and answered the questions I had regarding the paintings they also have a small gift shop that has some really nice books.
Small but very nice art museum
Great collection. A must to see museum.

Great park! Really really big with lots of places to host parties and events. Many playground choices too. Great for walks and feeding the ducks (though technically you're not supposed to do that). It's great

I LOVE this park. It’s absolutely beautiful, very large open spaces of grass, fun playgrounds for the kids to play and pretty ponds filled with ducks that you can go feed for fun. It’s also a lovely place for photo shoots, i frequently see families having photo shoots at this park and it’s beautiful. Especially right before sunset (golden hour) the lighting is perfect and the beautiful greenery makes for perfect photos. Great to just walk around and enjoy the day as well.

Excellent regional park with man made lakes, playgrounds, and walking paths. We like to ride our bikes around the many paths here - multiple options for loops. Also has some nice areas for picnics and parties. Definitely recommend.

It is a very well maintained park. It's always a pleasure to visit this park. The green areas are well maintained, water bodies are clean and safe for the water fowls and sheds are also well taken care of.

Very large public area and park. Has big gatherings sometimes on the weekends. Has duck ponds and play areas for kids. Great place to go and walk the trails, grab a picnic and invite friends, bring the kids for some play time or simply just hang out in the greenery and relax.
Very nice park. My niece and I ate lunch there. Beautiful!
Beautiful grass, very well kept especially for a girls JUSA soccer match.
This place was better than Disney world for us! The locals tell you everything you need to know!! Truly magical!!
Good park. Quiet and places for kids or bbqs. The equipment is old, so one star off.
It's a really great and safe place.

Lots of good restaurants and stores. Parking is fine until dinner time but even at its busiest there is usually still parking near the larger stores like 99 ranch and the pet store. Some of the restaurant spots seem to change yearly but usually thier replacements are just as good.
Lots of asian stores here.  The all you can eat Korean BBQ is very popular.

Attractive shopping plaza all year long. Featured by the popular Taiwanese/Chinese/Eastern Asian grocery store 99 Ranch Market etc. Too popular to park easily during holiday seasons and weekends. Many Taiwanese/Chinese  customers may drive long way to hear to their grocery shopping.
Everything you need in 1 shopping center - 99 Ranch for groceries, J Bakery for best breads, and Sam woo for best fancy dinner that we go to as a staple for family dinners.
Cool shopping area with well laid out parking area and stores

Parking is a little difficult because they are always busy. Great food with so many options from the bakery to hot pots to dumplings and dim sum. A great place to check out if you haven't already been here. It does get very busy during lunch, but it's worth the time!

I love the food in this plaza, but not the plaza itself. Always packed and some wild drivers. At night, a lot of parking are taken by people just hanging in front of their exotic cars. Really wish they did their meets at a less busy plaza.

Parking can be a bit challenging depending on time of day but there are so many delicious food choices to pick from it's worth the fight for a parking space. Korean, 85C, Curry, Dim Sum and much more. Definitely going back for more.

Restaurants are great but the place is way too crowded, as in 5 freeway rush hour crowded. Parking is almost impossible to find and there are long lines around the block. 

Pro tip: reserve ahead of time, Uber or Lyft your ride. This is the best way around this plaza. Do not drive yourself, it is like doing battle for parking spots.

It's definitely the culinary center of Irvine, especially if you enjoy different types of Asian cuisine, be it Taiwanese, Japanese, Korean, Vietnamese, Mainland Chinese, etc. Every single restaurant has its followers. I guess only the popular ones can survive there. The downside is that the parking can become a hassle during busy hours and lines can be long for some of the restaurants.

I really enjoyed this restaurant in downtown.  The service was very good and the vibe was very nice.  I ordered the squash fritters and beet salad and it was pretty good,  just didn't like the slate plates.  Roomy, fairly quiet,  large alcohol section too. I would definitely return.

Excellent, Excellent, Excellent! The atmosphere was wonderful, the music was great, the hospitality was awesome along with the excellent service. The food presentation was spectacular and the food was extremely deliciously. You will definitely want to return to The Market Place.
Stevie Parker,
Train Em Up Youth Enrichment Program.
Great atmosphere and friendly, helpful staff. The brunch menu is superb, especially the scallops! The service and the food were so great!

Brunch was delicious! Reservations are recommended. We were able to sit at the bar without one. Had the Eggs Benton and highly recommend it as a delicious breadless option. The roasted potatoes on my husband's dish were wonderful!

This was a party that we threw at the market place restaurant in Asheville North Carolina for my wife. Everything went perfect. The staff was great, food was great, atmosphere was great. We did the brunch that worked out fantastic! Thank you guys so much.

A great place to stop for a slice or a drink and hang out. There's much more than pizza on the menu including vegan options. The outdoor seating is good for larger groups and the bar style seating is perfect for solo diners looking to get in and out quick between classes. It's comfortable and casual but parking can be difficult near campus. Bring your friends and share a pie.
Been going here since I was a kid. I love this place. Great fresh pizza. Kids can watch it being made from the window outside. It's a nice, family-friendly dining experience.
Always wonderful.  If something isn't the way you expected, just let them know and they WILL fix it!!! Absolutely perfect experiences here!
Best place for pizza! We take all our friends and family here!! Small cozy family restaurant.
Awesome! A hidden gem near UC Irvine! Pizza was delicious and the service was spectacular!
The best set of wholesome choice supermarket. Just cost $12.99 (including tax). You almost have two meals. ( the size is large) I really love the well-done salmon and the chicken pastas~

Wholesome choice is one stop shopping for Iranians and other middle eastern folks within Irvine . Foods are medium quality groceries are good and fresh. Pastries are good and fresh. I would recommend this place if you do not care high price at cashiers.

Good store, bread, vegetable, fresh food, delis, pastries are good. There is room to improve in pricing and quality compare to other Persian Markets but compare to chain grocery stores they are much better.

It is very good market foodie people. All kinds of non veg like chicken, fish ..etc you can get here. Also they make some small dishes , you can taste fresh one. Vegetables are really fresh. I liked small oranges. Oranges are really sweet and not so expensive. Good place to hangout as well.

Great variety of Indian and Persian food. They even have a bakery where they make huge family sized bread. It is a must buy. They have a food court where they sell tasty Indian, Chinese and Persian delicacies. 

Must visit supermarket in Irvine

Good food and service in a nice location. After 9:15pm the lunch special is available again (about$15 before tax/tip), which is when I prefer to go. It's got all the kbbq necessities. Last call for ordering food is 11:20pm and you need to finish before midnight. Warning for large groups: there's a 3 card maximum for payment and for groups of 7 and more they auto charge 18% service fee.

Great selection of meats. Very helpful staff. Food is really good. I love coming here. Must have more than 1 person dining! Unfortunately, I dine alone often. This restaurant requires a minimum of 2 people for KBbq even during off peak hours. I walked in at 2 pm and a majority of tables were empty, but I was not seated because I was by myself. You must agree to ordering 2 items off the a la carte menu, which has 1 meat for $20-40. Not worth it. Again, if you have multiple people dining, it's a great place to order food, though they changed some of their meats and I think it's of lower quality than before. Just my opinion. Make sure you're ready to wait if you're dining during peak hours. Wait can be up to 1 hour.
Good food, service was good. Not too busy while I was there. I would recommend any of their marinated meats, they were all excellent.
Really good food. The place is bit small so often times you will have 20-30mins wait time but worth it. The sides given are really delicious too.

Staff was phenomenal, always by to check and see if you were taken care of and happy to accommodate special requests. Food was delicious (try the Curry Pork Belly and the Brisket). Prices are very fair and the selection was wide and delicious. Come here with a group of friends and enjoy yourself. Will definitely be back
